==German==
===Etymology===
Old High German [[hunt]], from common Germanic ''*hundaz'', from Proto-Indo-European {{IPAchar|''*ḱwn̥tós''}}, derived from {{IPAchar|''*ḱwō''}}, "dog". Near cognates include English [[hound]], Icelandic [[hundur]], and Gothic [[𐌷𐌿𐌽𐌳𐍃]] (hunds).

